Definition: If any of the subelements of DNAEncoding have values such as "Other", "User-defined"; or if DNAUserDefinedProfileAbstract is used, then DNACommentText is required to include detailed information about customized elements.
The DNA kit for the locus when the DNA profile is a composite profile from the typing results using different kits.
The Batch ID for the locus when the DNA profile is a composite profile from the typing results using different kits.
The DNA kit for the STR data when all loci are typed by the same kit
The Batch ID for the STR data when all loci are typed at the same time with the same batch ID
The container of all of the elements related to the distribution of the content messages.
An ellipse specified by a point, major axis, minor axis and rotation.
A gml:Polygon is a special surface that is defined by a single surface patch (see D.3.6). The boundary of this patch is coplanar and the polygon uses planar interpolation in its interior.
A gml:LineString is a special curve that consists of a single segment with linear interpolation. It is defined by two or more coordinate tuples, with linear interpolation between them.
A gml:Point is defined by a single coordinate tuple. The direct position of a point is specified by the gml:pos element which is of type gml:DirectPositionType.
